Harvard Medical School, USA

Bertarelli Program in Translational Neuroscience and Neuroengineering

 

 

The Bertarelli Program in Translational Neuroscience and Neuroengineering aims to push basic discoveries in biological mechanisms in neuroscience toward translational to clinical impact by creating stronger ties between basic neuroscientists, engineers and clinicians. The Program bridges two of the world’s great universities, namely Harvard University’s Medical School (HMS), with more than two centuries  of  leadership in alleviating human suffering caused by  disease, and the Ecole Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL), with special strength in engineering and technology. Read More…

NEWS

Bertarelli Symposium :

 

Mr. Matthias Tsai received a BMI fellowship to conduct his master thesis project in the laboratory of Professor Kreiman at Harvard University

 
- He will be working from February to August 2018 under the supervision of Prof. Gabriel Kreiman and will be co-supervised by Prof. Wulfram Gerstner from the BMI. The project will be directed at studying the task of visual pattern completion. This involves building computational models of the neural circuitry and applying computer vision architectures to replicate human performances. The investigation will also evaluate the application of generative systems to handle the problem of occluded object recognition.

BMI & Partners Annual PhD Students Neuroscience Symposium

As part of its effort to promote and enhance collaboration with its strategic partners, the BMI is organizing an annual PhD students’ symposium that will bring together PhD students from the BMI and its strategic partnering institutions. The symposium aims to provide the students with a forum to share their work, exchange ideas, explore collaborations, expand their network and discuss career and scientific topics of mutual interest. Read more...

 

International Student Exchange Program of the Brain Mind Institute

As part of its effort to promote and enhance scientific collaborations with its strategic partners, the BMI is launching an exchange program aimed at supporting master students from the BMI and partner institutions. Read more...

To apply:

Documents to be upload in PDF format (please indicate your last name at the beginning of each docs uploaded) :

• CV
• Statement of motivation
• Copy of your transcripts (grades)
• 1 Page description of the project
• 2 Recommendation letters (can also be sent by email to Prof. H. Lashuel: hilal.lashuel@epfl.ch)

Please fill out the application form and upload the requested documents here.
